Key Match Events: Victor Wembanyama ended the match against the Utah Jazz with a 25-point 5x5, 9 rebounds, 7 assists, 5 steals, and 5 blocks.
Post-Match Reflections: The San Antonio Spurs triumphed 106-88, marking their second win of the season (2-3)
Miscellaneous Highlights: Victor Wembanyama found his best game again after the bitter defeat against OKC, especially due to the clear loss against Chet Holmgren
Others: Chris Paul played very well, contributing 19 points and 10 assists in the game.
